						               													<description>&amp;quot;It is said that children who get lost in the city on a rainy day end up devoured by the sirains. The only way to escape those starving creatures is to find other lost kids and stay close to them at all times. It is also said that the sirains always find a way to seep into the most closely knit groups. By using evil thoughts, fear, hunger and loneliness, they lure their victims and snatch them, one by one, to devour them in the dark. In the end, only one lost child will find his way home. The others will never be seen again.&amp;quot; Lost in the rain is a short roleplaying game of sadness and horror which invites you to take on the role of a child, lost in the great city and hunted by mysterious creatures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player gets ten tokens at the start of the game. When a player loses their last token, the sirains eat them. Each turn (called a chapter) a player will be the main child for this chapter. The other players will play their child but also the sirains and the environment. Every time a player describes something that is frightening or harmful for the main child, the main child loses one token.&amp;#10;When only one child remains, their player can describe how their child finds the way back to their home.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
